The best professor ever. She might not be the best instructor, but for sure she is the best professor. She is extremely approachable outside of class, and she takes efforts to remember students name. She welcomes you to her office hrs, and will stay behind to help you even though the office hrs have ended. She won't kill you in exams as well.

You can get a great grade in her course with learning basically nothing.  I had a friend in A30 & they learned more & sometimes harder material. Keep her away from math & CS  people!!--the one's that need to learn this

She is very caring and understanding. I had some problem understanding the material, but thankfully she was able to help me out with it. Her explanations are clear and concise. What many students do wrong is approach her when its too late. If you need or want help, go to her asap. Do not wait until the last minute to seek her assistance.

rComments: I thoroughly enjoyed this class; her teaching style was neat, concise, and approachable. She turned a basic analysis course from something to be feared, to something feasible, with some hard work. Get past the heavy accent, and I definitely recommend Prof Shahbazi to any aspiring mathematics student!

I have not had her as a Professor but she's always willing to help in the Math Aid Centre (near the ARC). She's really nice and genuinely wants you to understand the material! I asked her many questions and she was always willing to help!
